HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1211
By Martin G
A RESOLUTION to recognize Joe Smith on the occasion of his
retirement.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
honor those citizens who have performed with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm throughout
their years of public service; and
WHEREAS, Joe Smith is one such estimable person, who has served the citizens of
District 3 in Hamilton County with distinction over the past ten years as a member of the
Hamilton County Schools Board of Education; and
WHEREAS, during his fruitful tenure, Mr. Smith served on the Hamilton County Schools
Board of Education with acumen and alacrity, first as a member, then as vice chairman for two
years, and most recently as chairman for three years, in which roles he always endeavored to
prioritize children and serve in their best interest; and
WHEREAS, for a decade, Mr. Smith was a driving force behind boosting student
achievement, supporting strategic planning and budget leadership, improving transportation and
operations, and investing in employee culture; and
WHEREAS, in 2019, Hamilton County Schools became the fastest-improving district in
the State with record TVAAS growth, showing proficiency increases in all core subjects, with
more than half of the schools meeting or exceeding growth expectations; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Smith proudly supported the development and implementation of Future
Ready Institutes and Opportunity 2030 to expand innovative career pathways in area high
schools; championed historic TISA funding investments to support students, teachers, and
classroom needs; endorsed opportunities that raised student scholarships from $66 million in
HJR1211
015788
- 1 -

2015 to more than $184 million in 2024; and supported programs that have led to a ninety-four-
percent graduation rate, the highest in the district's history; and
WHEREAS, under his astute guidance, Hamilton County Schools not only experienced a
dramatic rise in student athletics success, increasing state championships sixfold since 2015
and upgrading school athletic facilities throughout the county, but also became a regional leader
in school transportation; and
WHEREAS, Joe Smith supported expansion to nineteen community schools, providing
wraparound services through partners such as Northside Neighborhood House, OnPoint, the
University of Tennessee at Chattanooga, and Communities In Schools; and
WHEREAS, in addition to providing long-term community solutions through major facility
projects, capital investments, and infrastructure improvements, Mr. Smith helped raise the
district's employee retention rate and implement both health and mental health programs to
support employees; and
WHEREAS, his many professional accomplishments aside, Mr. Smith is most grateful
for the love and support of his wife, Paula Smith; and
WHEREAS, Joe Smith exemplifies the spirit and allegiance to family and community that
are characteristic of a true Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, throughout his estimable career, Mr. Smith has demonstrated the utmost
professionalism, ability, and integrity, winning the unbridled respect and admiration of his
colleagues and the citizens of Hamilton County; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Joe Smith for ten years of dedicated public
service as a member of the Hamilton County Schools Board of Education and wish him every
continued success in his future endeavors.
- 2 - 015788

BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
